description: Returns the list of images that you have access to. Newly created images can take up to two minutes to appear in the ListImages API Results.

parameters.name: filters
parameters.description: Use the following filters to streamline results: name osVersion platform type version (dict) --- A filter name and value pair that is used to return a more specific list of results from a list operation. Filters can be used to match a set of resources by specific criteria, such as tags, attributes, or IDs. name (string) --- The name of the filter. Filter names are case-sensitive. values (list) --- The filter values. Filter values are case-sensitive. (string) ---

nested_items.name: requestId
nested_items.description: The request ID that uniquely identifies this request.

nested_items.name: imageVersionList
nested_items.description: The list of image semantic versions.

nested_items.name: arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of a specific version of an Image Builder image.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: The name of this specific version of an Image Builder image.

nested_items.name: type
nested_items.description: Specifies whether this image produces an AMI or a container image.

nested_items.name: version
nested_items.description: Details for a specific version of an Image Builder image. This version follows the semantic version syntax.

nested_items.name: platform
nested_items.description: The operating system platform of the image version, for example 'Windows' or 'Linux'.

nested_items.name: osVersion
nested_items.description: The operating system version of the Amazon EC2 build instance. For example, Amazon Linux 2, Ubuntu 18, or Microsoft Windows Server 2019.

nested_items.name: owner
nested_items.description: The owner of the image version.

nested_items.name: dateCreated
nested_items.description: The date on which this specific version of the Image Builder image was created.

nested_items.name: buildType
nested_items.description: Indicates the type of build that created this image. The build can be initiated in the following ways:

nested_items.name: imageSource
nested_items.description: The origin of the base image that Image Builder used to build this image.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: The next token used for paginated responses. When this field isn't empty, there are additional elements that the service hasn't included in this request. Use this token with the next request to retrieve additional objects.
